11/05/2011
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The defence ministry announced on Tuesday (May 10th) that a Romanian soldier has died in a blast in southern Afghanistan.
Catalin Ionel Marinescu died of wounds from an improvised explosive device that blew up as he was inspecting a bridge in the province of Zabul.
He is the second Romanian to die in Afghanistan in a week.
(Adevarul, Cotidianul, Realitatea - 10/05/11)
